"{\"uid\": \"nbcsports.com-olympics-news-triathlon-olympic-team-usa-paris-2024\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Triathletes Taylor Spivey, Kirsten Kasper and Seth Rider are headed to their first Olympics, completing the U.S. team for Paris.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 128, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 27, \"end\": 41, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsten_Kasper\", \"score\": 0.9999994173896872, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kirsten Kasper\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsten_Kasper\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kirsten_Kasper\"}, {\"begin\": 122, \"end\": 127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5300620658793538e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They join Taylor Knibb and Morgan Pearson, who previously qualified by finishing in the top eight at the Olympic test event in Paris last August.\", \"from\": 130, \"to\": 275, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 140, \"end\": 152, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}, {\"begin\": 157, \"end\": 171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Pearson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Morgan Pearson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Pearson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Morgan_Pearson\"}, {\"begin\": 257, \"end\": 262, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5300620658793538e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Spivey, Kasper and Rider were chosen by a USA Triathlon selection committee.\", \"from\": 277, \"to\": 353, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 319, \"end\": 332, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0172288851184326e-20, \"text\": \"USA Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Selections were made based on results during the Olympic qualification period over the last two years.\", \"from\": 354, \"to\": 456, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The top American women in this season's World Series rankings are Knibb (second in the world), Spivey (sixth) and Kasper (11th).\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 466, \"end\": 474, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"score\": 0.9989531975775966, \"rank\": 0.0010461510016257594, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\"}, {\"begin\": 524, \"end\": 529, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.755745853298091e-28, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"LIST:U.S. athletes qualified for Paris Olympics  Spivey and Kasper bolstered their Olympic chances by placing fourth and fifth at a World Series stop in Yokohama, Japan, on May 11.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 768, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 621, \"end\": 635, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 749, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"score\": 0.9628235795906538, \"rank\": 0.038607106027918975, \"text\": \"Yokohama\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\"}, {\"begin\": 751, \"end\": 756, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9980151129329599, \"rank\": 0.0018052796543700192, \"text\": \"Japan\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japan_women's_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"If one had made the podium there, she would have automatically qualified for Paris.\", \"from\": 769, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 846, \"end\": 851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999999745341, \"rank\": 2.5300620658793538e-11, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But then Tokyo Olympic bronze medalist Katie Zaferes beat both Spivey and Kasper at the most recent World Series stop on May 25 in Cagliari, Italy.\", \"from\": 854, \"to\": 1001, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 863, \"end\": 868, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7275571038311736, \"rank\": 0.3744625583928563, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 893, \"end\": 906, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Zaferes\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Zaferes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Zaferes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Zaferes\"}, {\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 993, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.700993649948352e-12, \"text\": \"Cagliari\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\"}, {\"begin\": 995, \"end\": 1000, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9978690497217284, \"rank\": 0.001575851489592779, \"text\": \"Italy\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Italy_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Zaferes, who returned to competition in March 2023 after July 2022 childbirth, placed 12th in Cagliari ahead of Spivey (15th) and Kasper (21st).\", \"from\": 1003, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\", \"score\": 0.9999999999954525, \"rank\": 4.700993649948352e-12, \"text\": \"Cagliari\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cagliari_Calcio\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ultimately, the committee went with Spivey and Kasper over Zaferes.\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1216, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago at this time, Zaferes and Spivey were ranked Nos.\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1283, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"1 and 2 in the world, but only one spot was left on the U.S. Olympic team.\", \"from\": 1284, \"to\": 1358, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Zaferes was the discretionary selection that time.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1409, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Going into this Olympic cycle, I wanted to make sure I did everything I could to earn a spot on the team,\\\" Spivey said, according to USA Triathlon.\", \"from\": 1411, \"to\": 1559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1545, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0172288851184326e-20, \"text\": \"USA Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In 2020, I was so close and felt like it was within reach and it was so heartbreaking that I wasn't selected.\\\"\", \"from\": 1560, \"to\": 1671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"After Spivey, Kasper was the next-highest ranked American to miss the team for Tokyo.\", \"from\": 1673, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1722, \"end\": 1730, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"score\": 0.9989531975775966, \"rank\": 0.0010461510016257594, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6631808\", \"Q623109\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/American_League\"}, {\"begin\": 1752, \"end\": 1757, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7275571038311736, \"rank\": 0.3744625583928563, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This is my third time trying to make the Olympic team and this really shows that dreams do come true,\\\" Kasper said, according to USA Triathlon.\", \"from\": 1760, \"to\": 1904, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1890, \"end\": 1903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0172288851184326e-20, \"text\": \"USA Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gwen Jorgensen, the 2016 Olympic gold medalist, ended a six-year triathlon retirement in early 2023 to bid for the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1906, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1906, \"end\": 1920, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gwen_Jorgensen\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gwen Jorgensen\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gwen_Jorgensen\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gwen_Jorgensen\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She placed 15th in Yokohama and is ranked 23rd in the world, three spots behind Zaferes.\", \"from\": 2035, \"to\": 2123, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2054, \"end\": 2062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"score\": 0.9628235795906538, \"rank\": 0.038607106027918975, \"text\": \"Yokohama\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On the men's side, Rider is ranked 26th overall and third among Americans in this season's World Series behind Pearson and Matt McElroy.\", \"from\": 2125, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Rider, 27, competed at the 2014 Youth Olympics and was part of a bronze-medal-winning U.S. team at the 2022 Mixed Relay World Championships.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In 2014 I represented the U.S. at the Youth Olympic Games and it felt like a miniature Olympics,\\\" Rider said, according to USA Triathlon.\", \"from\": 2405, \"to\": 2543, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2444, \"end\": 2463, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.7972606153143791, \"rank\": 0.2489198204153415, \"text\": \"Youth Olympic Games\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Youth_Olympic_Games\"}, {\"begin\": 2529, \"end\": 2542, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0172288851184326e-20, \"text\": \"USA Triathlon\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/USA_Triathlon\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That's what really sparked my Olympic dream.\", \"from\": 2544, \"to\": 2589, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's crazy to have something that I have been thinking about and dreaming about daily for the past 10 years become a reality.\", \"from\": 2590, \"to\": 2715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I still do not think it's hit me.\\\"\", \"from\": 2716, \"to\": 2750, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"McElroy just missed the team for a second consecutive Olympics.\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2815, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Never give up,\\\" was posted on his Instagram later Wednesday afternoon.\", \"from\": 2817, \"to\": 2888, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2852, \"end\": 2861, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.193187633521969e-17, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Three years ago, McElroy was also in contention for the last U.S. Olympic men's spot that ultimately went to Kevin McDowell.\", \"from\": 2890, \"to\": 3014, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2999, \"end\": 3013, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_McDowell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kevin McDowell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_McDowell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kevin_McDowell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McDowell then placed sixth in Tokyo, the best finish for a U.S. man since triathlon made its Olympic debut in 2000.\", \"from\": 3016, \"to\": 3131, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3016, \"end\": 3024, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"score\": 0.9998749055317973, \"rank\": 7.235584329840899e-05, \"text\": \"McDowell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\"}, {\"begin\": 3046, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.7275571038311736, \"rank\": 0.3744625583928563, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Knibb, Pearson, McDowell and Zaferes also combined to take silver in the first Olympic triathlon relay event.\", \"from\": 3132, \"to\": 3241, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3132, \"end\": 3137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.755745853298091e-28, \"text\": \"Knibb\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Knibb\"}, {\"begin\": 3148, \"end\": 3156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"score\": 0.9998749055317973, \"rank\": 7.235584329840899e-05, \"text\": \"McDowell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McDowell competed in two World Series events since the start of 2023, failing to finish one in March 2023 and placing 47th in Yokohama on May 11.\", \"from\": 3243, \"to\": 3388, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3243, \"end\": 3251, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"score\": 0.9998749055317973, \"rank\": 7.235584329840899e-05, \"text\": \"McDowell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Irvin_McDowell\"}, {\"begin\": 3369, \"end\": 3377, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"score\": 0.9628235795906538, \"rank\": 0.038607106027918975, \"text\": \"Yokohama\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Yokohama_Rubber_Company\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was set back by sickness, injuries and September surgery for a torn ankle ligament.\", \"from\": 3389, \"to\": 3475, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Globally, French triathletes have impressed going into a home Games.\", \"from\": 3477, \"to\": 3545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3487, \"end\": 3493, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9804030785792603, \"rank\": 0.012063007528162745, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Leo Bergere is ranked No.\", \"from\": 3547, \"to\": 3572, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3547, \"end\": 3550, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Wyatt\", \"score\": 0.998628591944514, \"rank\": 0.0008597169385838087, \"text\": \"Leo\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Wyatt\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leo_Wyatt\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"1 in the world for the men, though he is No.\", \"from\": 3573, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"5 in